<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n06043c"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n06" href="#n06043c">N06 (VI.B.11)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n06all.htm#n06043c"> 43(c)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> play shop / &mdash; houses</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Ma petite fille de quatre ans, &eacute;crit une m&egrave;re, <mark>jouait</mark> un jour <mark>&ldquo;&agrave; la boutique&rdquo;</mark> avec sa plus jeune sour, au moment o&ugrave; j&apos;entrais dans la chambre. L&apos;a&icirc;n&eacute;e &eacute;tait le marchand, je m&apos;approche d&apos;elle et l&apos;embrasse. Elle &eacute;clate en sanglots: &ldquo;Maman, tu n&apos;embrasses jamais l&apos;homme dans la boutique.&rdquo; Mon baiser avait g&acirc;t&eacute; son illusion. <font color="green">[My four-year-old daughter, a mother wrote, was playing &ldquo;in the shop&rdquo; with her youngest sister when I entered the room. The eldest was the merchant, I approach her and kiss her. She burst into tears: &ldquo;Mom, you never kiss the man in the shop.&rdquo; My kiss had spoiled his illusion.]</font> <small> Fr&eacute;d&eacute;ric Queyrat, <a name="FQLJ" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#FQLJ"><cite title="source">Les Jeux des Enfants</cite></a> (1920) 67</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
